                <note rend="inline" type="source">551.5F1/158: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                        Minister in Switzerland</hi> (<persName type="to">
                        <hi rend="italic">Wilson</hi>
                    </persName>)</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Paraphrase]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1931-09-16T16:00:00-04:00"
                            >September 16, 1931—4 p.m.</date>
                    </dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>108. Legation’s 128, September 14, 11 p.m. The application of you and Davis to
                    the task of bringing a silver conference resolution before the League Council is
                    highly appreciated. Your telegram of September 14 refers to the readiness of
                    India to cooperate toward a stabilization of silver prices. Since opinion in
                    Britain seems to favor cooperation on this issue, our belief is that the
                    resolution you plan to offer might delay matters beyond the time set in our
                    telegram 101 of September 3, 4 p.m. Please advise whether you feel that a study
                    by the Finance Committee would prove harmful, should resort be made to direct
                    negotiation with interested Governments. If so, our suggestion is for you to
                    informally request Davis to proceed no further.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Stimson</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
